# Development Rules

## Before You Code

1. Read `AI_RULES.md`, relevant `docs/plan/`, and `docs/context/`.
2. Do not implement without an approved Plan in `docs/plan/`.
3. Explain **Why**, **What**, and **Impact** before significant changes.
4. Never overwrite files without stating what changed and why.

## Workflow

```
Understand → Plan → Build → Test → Review → Document
```

- **Reuse** `templates/` and existing `src/` modules before writing new code.
- Keep changes scoped to the request — no drive-by refactors.
- Run `npm run lint` and `npm run build` when applicable.

## Coding Standards

- Readable code over clever code
- Small, single-responsibility modules
- Strong TypeScript typing — avoid `any`
- Consistent, role-revealing names
- No duplicated logic — extract shared utilities

## Next.js 16

- Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using Next.js APIs
- Do not use deprecated APIs or Pages Router patterns
- Keep business logic in `src/` — `app/` is routing and composition only

## Application Code

- Do not create `src/` code unless explicitly requested
- Route Handlers delegate to `src/application/` use cases
- Match patterns in `agents/Builder.md`
